<p align="center"><h2><span id="title">Raster Unification </span></h2><img id="icon" src="../icons/maxent.png" /></p>

<p><span id="section">Brief Description</span></p>

Unifies any number of input raster layers to a common extent and no-data value. Also be used in the MAXENT data preperation. 
Method is based on an idea from <a href="http://ssrebelious.wordpress.com/2012/09/02/raster-extent-modification-using-qgis/">Yury Ryabov</a>, who provided the code for this script.

</p>
<p><span id="section">Parameters</span></p>
<ul>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input Raster Layers: </span> Any numbers of raster layers</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Nodata value: </span> Choose a common no-data value for all layers</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span> Output Folder: </span> All unified raster layers will be saved in this folder and added to QGIS in the end. </p>
	</li>	
</ul>

</ul></p>

<p>
